article_title: UnitedHealth's $43 Billion Exit From Fee-For-Service Medicine

article_metadata.author: Bruce Japsen

og.description: Continuing the health insurance industry’s march further away from fee-for-service medicine, UnitedHealth Group (UNH) executives said this week they will increase value-based payments to doctors and hospitals by 20 percent this year to “north of $43 billion.” UnitedHealth, considered a barometer for the health insurance industry given its size, is rapidly [...]
